[Name] Berkeley DB
[Summary] Provides embedded database support for traditional and client/server application
[License] OSI Approved
[Description] Berkeley DB (libdb) is a programmatic toolkit that
provides embedded database support for both
traditional and client/server applications. It
includes b+tree, queue, extended linear hashing,
fixed, and variable-length record access methods,
transactions, locking, logging, shared memory
caching and database recovery. DB supports C, C++,
Java, and Perl APIs. It is available for a wide
variety of UNIX platforms as well as Windows NT
and Windows '95 (MSVC 4, 5 and 6).
[Homepage] http://www.sleepycat.com/
